  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6817 trading 39 points below the GEX flip at 6856, dealers are currently in long gamma mode and likely buying this dip after the -3.5% 1-minute drop. The massive positive gamma wall at 6900 (+5.6B) creates a strong ceiling where dealers will aggressively sell any rallies, while the 6755 negative gamma floor (-1.47B) provides downside support through dealer buying. Key levels to watch: break above 6856 flips dealers to short gamma and opens path to 6900 resistance, while a break below 6755 could trigger accelerated selling.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect the market to bounce back toward 6850-6900 range with dealers providing stabilizing flows.",
